<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="237" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,757,1538,2069]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,1538,1562]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[284,572,1538,1561]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Enguterothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fuscipalpis">
<emphasis box="[284,572,1538,1561]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Enguterothrix fuscipalpis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described on the basis of two females from 
<collectingCountry box="[577,661,1569,1592]" name="Uganda" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Uganda</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Denis J." journalOrPublisher="Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" pagination="169 - 203" part="65" refString="Denis J. 1962. Notes sur les erigonides. XX. Erigonides d'Afrique orientale avec quelques remarques sur les erigonides ethiopiens. Revue de Zoologie et de Botanique Africaines 65: 169 - 203." title="Notes sur les erigonides. XX. Erigonides d'Afrique orientale avec quelques remarques sur les erigonides ethiopiens" type="journal article" year="1962">Denis, 1962</bibRefCitation>
) and was incorrectly placed in this genus. The 
<typeStatus box="[151,244,1633,1656]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">holotype</typeStatus>
(the 
<typeStatus box="[302,394,1634,1658]" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">paratype</typeStatus>
was not seen) does not belong to 
<taxonomicName box="[151,300,1665,1688]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Enguterothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,300,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Enguterothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which is supported by a different formula of chaetotaxy and by a dissimilar epigyne conformation. Moreover, I could not find any other 
<taxonomicName box="[605,756,1728,1751]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Enguterothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[605,756,1728,1751]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Enguterothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens among the Afrotropical linyphiids that I have seen so far, therefore I preliminarily place this species in 
<taxonomicName box="[270,382,1825,1848]" class="Arachnida" family="Linyphiidae" genus="Micrargus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="2" pageNumber="237" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[270,382,1825,1848]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Micrargus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The transfer is supported by the same chaetotaxy (2.2.1.1), lack of the trichobothrium on metatarsus IV, similar value of the TmI (0.35), as well as the similar epigyne conformation, namely, the presence of a large epigynal cavity (see 
<figureCitation box="[619,686,1950,1975]" captionStart="Fig. 1" captionStartId="2.[831,866,1078,1099]" captionTargetBox="[882,1383,259,1036]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[831,1436,254,1045]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Micrargus fuscipalpis (Denis, 1962) comb. nov., female holotype. Abdomen, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/269415/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="237">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
). The discovery of the corresponding male will throw more light on the systematic position of this species within the linyphiids.
</paragraph>
